    <p>Main­tain­ing a bal­anced diet not only keeps you healthy, but it can also lift one’s mood.</p>
    <p>Ac­cord­ing to a study pub­lished in the journal Nu­tri­tional Neu­ro­science in 2015, foods rich in omega-3 fatty acids, nuts, beans and whole­grain cereal can help pre­vent de­pres­sion.</p>
    <p>Dr Naras Lap­sys, a con­sul­tant di­eti­tian at The Well­ness Clinic, sug­gests 10 foods that can help boost one’s mood.</p>


